Date:9/21/2004 6:15:43 PM
From:Jurgis Bekepuris
This was not addressed to me, so hope you don't mind. :)

I think exit strategy for oils is much more unclear than for other companies.
In other companies, I can see whether something is overvalued. In oil (and
other commodity companies), a company may look overvalued based on current
commodity price, but be cheap if the commodity price goes up (and vice versa -
so there is additional risk if commodity price declines).

Otherwise, I sell when my metrics show that the expected annual return is lower
than 7-5% (depends on company). I also sell if there is a change in the company
that makes me change my mind about holding it.

Good luck

Jurgis
