%EOM----------------------

%BOM---------------------
Date:9/23/2004 11:48:15 AM
From:E_K_S
Hi dstange -I use the Street Smart Pro package that Schwab provides. I set up
my time series screen with the price, bollenger bands and MA in the top screen
and volume and on-balance volume AVG on the bottom part of the screen.

You can really use any "On-Balance" volume indicator but it is most effective
over a long time series 36 months. When you can see a double bottom formation
with lower volume on the lower low, the on-balance volume s/b at an extreme
low.

This formation also works on 18 month charts ( 100 weeks) too. The shorter the
time slice, the less accurate the indicator is since it takes several months
for the strong hands to eventually throw in the towel.

When the on-balance volume is at a high extreme, all the news is good, the
stock is near an all time high and everybody is talking about the company. This
is a good signal that the company is probably over valued and ready for a fall
back to its mean price.

Do a simple Google search on "On-Balance Volume" and you will find many better
definitions that I have provided here.

Hope that helps.

EKS
