Date:9/27/2004 1:59:56 AM
From:Spekulatius
re IMOS -
difficult to value the company/stock due to the volatility of their business.
Stock seems cheap if one anualizes their last quarterly earnings (PE around 5).
IMOS business (as well as it's peer SPIL) is a contractor for packaging and
testing, a very competitive and capital intense business with gross margins
south of 30%. Because of the business IMOS is in, they will have problems to
generate Free Cash flows. For those reasons, I don't like the business
prospects of IMOS too much, but i do acknowledge that it may be a good play on
a recovery in semis.

For a semi company to be investment grade (at least for me), I like to see
gross margins of around 50% or more, which is only consitently achievable by
companies with a sustainable competitive advantage (MXIM, LLTC, ADI,
ISIL,TXN,ALTR, XLNX fall into this category(.
