Date:10/8/2004 11:42:03 AM
From:Spekulatius
 re economic moat 
The concept of "moat" which sort of was conered from Warren E Buffet is an
important one. it manifest itself usually with the opportunity (if management
does not screw up) to achieve above average ROI and/or growth rates in the
future. I agree that the rear window view can be very misleading, examples
where the rear view did not work are pharmas like BMY and now potentially MRK.

Unfortunately I think cencept of moat is often misused, especially by biotech
and technology companies. Companies like MLNM have been taking about franchises
even before they had products on the market. In technology, there are very few
true moat companies - examples are INTC, CSCO or the analog semis like LLTC and
MXIM. On the other hand remember ARIBA, HGSI, GLBC?
